  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Covid-19 Support- MeDRA</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">MeDRA to assist in humanitarian assistance towards COVID-19 mitigation in providing food handouts, water and non food items to make the center comfortable and curb people who are reportedly escaping from the quarantine centres.
In addition, there is need to capacitate personnel that mann the center and health workers responsible to providing service to the quarantined people. Further, provision of psychosocial support for the returnees during the 21 days is increasingly needed to distress them as well as to provide entertainment. To reduce social tension in the community where the quarantine center ie Duma residential areas, awareness raising of COVID-19 will be done through public address. This will also help in reducing stigmatization and rejection of the returnees in the center.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">improved capacity of Healthcare workers in identifying and case management of covid-19
Improved awareness of communities on COVID-19 and reduction of stigma of people in center

Increased access to hand washing facilities
Improved health and hygiene practices of the people in quarantine centers
Improved health and hygiene practices of the people in quarantine centers
Improved access to water
Increased access to food to avoid individuals from escaping from the center
Improved capacity of affected people to cope with distress during the 21 days of quarantine
Improved access to basic medical supplies</narrative>
  </description>
